Outspoken musician Ntsiki Mazwai has weighed in on the ANC war room debacle labelling ANC activist Shaka Sisulu and Kay Sexwale as spoilt rich kids with entitlement and privilege issues . Sisulu and Sexwale were reported to have been part of a secret public relations war room an alleged smear campaign set up by the ANC to allegedly discredit opposition parties ahead of last year s local government elections.Both parties have denied their involvement in the saga but that did not stop the outspoken Ntsiki Mazwai from taking to Twitter to criticise the pairhttps://twitter.com/ntsikimazwai/status/823884616964730881?ref src=twsrc%5Etfwthese are spoilt rich kids trying to be something guys&#8230;&#8230;lol! https://t.co/KrZZd3rgEb&mdash; Imbongikazi yeSizwe (@ntsikimazwai) January 24, 2017lets be honest shaka sisulu and kay sexwale r those opinionated kids that come from a rich family and have entitlement and privilege issues&mdash; Imbongikazi yeSizwe (@ntsikimazwai) January 24, 2017Ntsiki went on to warn fans about people who pretend to act perfect describing it as a shaka sisulu charm .careful of ppl who act perfect&#8230;&#8230;.that shaka sisulu charm should have told you LIGHTS, CAMERA&#8230;..ACTION! lol!&mdash; Imbongikazi yeSizwe (@ntsikimazwai) January 24, 2017Details of the alleged war room were contained in an urgent court application brought before the Johannesburg High Court on Tuesday by Sihle Bolani. Bolani claimed that her services were used by the ANC during the elections and demanded R2.2-million in payment. The application was dismissed.Shaka took to Twitter on Tuesday to deny the war room claims calling them fake news . He promised to address the speculation on a TV show he co-hosted but did not appear on the show as promised.